Class 8

Loops in Java:
	while
	do while
	for
	enhanced for

while loop we use when we don’t know how many times the action should be repeated

int a=1;

while(a<=5){

	code;
	a++;//2, 3, 4, 5, 6
}
--------------------------------------------------------
int b=1;

while(b<=5){

	code;
	b--;// 0, -1, -2, -3
}

do while loop we use when we don’t know how many times the action should be repeated

int c=1;

do {

	code;
	c++;
}while(c>5);


do while vs while

while check condition first and then does action if condition is true
do while does action and then check condition

Good Morning 5 times;

for (int i=1; i<=5; i++) {
	System.out.println("Good Morning");
}

Keywords that can be used inside loops

break --> breaks loop and skips all code that you have after break inside the loop

continue --> skip 1 iteration

Nested Loops

for (int i=1; i<3; i++){

			System.out.println("I am an outer loop ");

			for (int y=0; y<=3; y++) {

				System.out.println("I am an inner loop ");
			}

}













